727311f-b.title: Queens: Main Street - Sanford Avenue
727311f-b.text:
Main Street, at the S. E. corner of Sanford Avenue, showing
a colontal home. Wolverton's 1891 map shows the house to have
been owned by C. King. View 3 shows the SanSord Avenue side of
the house..
View 1: April 8, 1927
View 2,3: October 23, 1930
P. L. Sperr
727311f-b.folder: Main Street & Sanford Avenue, Queens, NY

727954f-c.title: Queens: Sanford Avenue - Main Street
727954f-c.text:
(1)
Sanford Ave. (foreground), south side, just east of Main Street,
showing a view of the Joseph Harris King house in 1873. It was
demolished in 1932.
October 11, 1930.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2) (3) and (4)
The same from different angles. Joseph Harris King was, in
1860, a partner in the firm of King and Ripley which owned the Bloodgood
Nursery which was established in 1798 by James Bloodgood.
View 2: 1922.
View 3: February 1925.
View 4: October 11, 1930.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
